answers.answer: Hi,The test results mean that there are antibodies in the system that predispose you to development of Type 1 diabetes in the future, even though the ICA was negative.Other tests that should be done right now include simultaneous fasting glucose and c-peptide levels, which will help determine if there are already abnormal glucose levels, and how much insulin production is still present in the body.Hope this helps.Take care.
